race.comment: Competitive. LARSEN BAY (12) brings the best recent figures and just missed last time in an Open at Manangatang over this distance. Has more weight but maps well and this is winnable. A DIME APPROACH (2) peaks and will appreciate the step up to the middle distance. Has the blinkers on again and finally draws an inside gate. AMERICAN GAS (7) races forward and has been racing at Warrnambool in better grade since the Maiden win there. Well placed and is sure to give a sight. ASEVENTY SEVEN (3) finds easier and will be suited stepping up from a mile. On a 7-day return and rates a player. STEP IN TIME (4) is a former Kiwi on a 35 day return and her deserves a betting watch.
